2
00:00:38,970 --> 00:00:40,800
至今我的生活是这样的:
Here's my day so far:

3
00:00:40,970 --> 00:00:43,640
蹲过大牢 失去过梦中情人
Went to jail, lost the girl of my dreams,

4
00:00:43,810 --> 00:00:46,110
被狠狠扁过
and got my butt kicked pretty good.

5
00:00:46,750 --> 00:00:49,810
仍然 事情变得更加糟糕
Still, things could be a lot worse.

6
00:00:51,180 --> 00:00:52,550
噢 对了
Oh, that's right.

7
00:00:53,150 --> 00:00:54,950
我就要摔成肉饼了
I'm falling to my death.

8
00:00:55,590 --> 00:00:56,990
不是吧
Guess they can't.

9
00:00:57,720 --> 00:00:59,420
你也许会问 怎会如此结局? 
How'd it all come to this, you ask?

10
00:01:00,790 --> 00:01:02,490
结局早已是注定的
My end starts at the beginning.

11
00:01:03,260 --> 00:01:04,660
从最初就注定了
The very beginning.

12
00:01:08,330 --> 00:01:10,200
是的 那就是我
Yes, that's me.

13
00:01:10,970 --> 00:01:13,670
我有一个非常正常的童年
I had a fairly standard childhood.

14
00:01:14,770 --> 00:01:17,680
我出生于 你们所说的破碎的家庭
I came from, what you might call, a broken home.

15
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:20,600
字面意义上的破碎
Literally broken.

16
00:01:21,180 --> 00:01:24,150
我在八天大的时候 我还和我的双亲在一起
I was eight days old and still living with my parents.

17
00:01:24,920 --> 00:01:26,510
很悲剧吧
How sad is that?

18
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:28,780
显然这个时候该改变了
Clearly it was time to move on.

19
00:01:28,950 --> 00:01:31,720
这是你的跟班 他会照顾你的
Here is your minion. He will take care of you.

20
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:33,320
还有 这个是你的奶嘴
And here is your binky.

21
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:36,260
你的命运是...
You are destined for...

22
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:40,660
我没有听清楚最后的那一部分 不过听起来很重要
I didn't quite hear that last part, but it sounded important.

23
00:01:40,830 --> 00:01:43,460
...二 一 - 命运是啥? 
...two, one. - Destined for what?

24
00:01:45,270 --> 00:01:47,970
我出发去寻找我的人生
I set out to find my destiny.

25
00:01:49,610 --> 00:01:53,840
另一个格兰普象限的小鬼与我的想法完全一致
Turns out a kid from the Glaupunkt quadrant had the exact same idea.

26
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:04,250
就是那天我遇到了大好人先生...
That was the day I met Mr. Goody Two- Shoes...

27
00:02:06,790 --> 00:02:11,630
...那时我们闪亮的人生轨迹开始了
...and our glorious rivalry was born.

28
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:18,570
难道这个就是我命运? 
Could this be what I was destined for?

29
00:02:18,940 --> 00:02:21,200
奢华的梦幻般的生活
A dream life filled with luxury.

30
00:02:23,210 --> 00:02:24,510
显然不是的
Apparently not.

31
00:02:25,980 --> 00:02:27,950
就连命运也会按喜好挑选
Even fate picks its favorites.

32
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:30,580
没啥
No big deal.

33
00:02:31,380 --> 00:02:33,410
一个截然不同的人生等着我
A much different fate awaited me.

34
00:02:41,930 --> 00:02:44,830
宝宝 真体贴
A baby! How thoughtful.

35
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,760
噢 是的 是的 我看到了它就想到了你
Oh, yes. Yes, I saw it and thought of you.

36
00:02:48,770 --> 00:02:51,700
幸运的是 我找到了一个小小的一个叫家的地方
Luckily I found a lovely little place to call home.

37
00:02:51,870 --> 00:02:53,030
我们能留下它么
Can we keep it?

38
00:02:54,140 --> 00:02:56,770
这个地方教育我对和错
A place that taught me the differences between right...

39
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:59,270
的区别
...and wrong.

40
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:01,770
大好人先生
Mr. Goody Two- Shoes, on the other hand,

41
00:03:01,950 --> 00:03:04,440
过着衣来伸手饭来张口的日子
had life handed to him on a silver platter.

42
00:03:04,620 --> 00:03:06,080
我们的宝宝会飞呀
Our baby can fly.

43
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:08,480
是的 是的 你的宝宝最强了 亲爱的
Yes, yes, nothing but the best for you, darling.

44
00:03:08,690 --> 00:03:12,920
飞行能力 刀枪不入 无敌发型
The power of flight, invulnerability, and great hair.

45
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:17,260
我又更加更加强的本领
But I had something far, far greater.

46
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,730
强大的智慧......
My amazing intellect...

47
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:22,420
...我有能制造破坏力超强的工具
...and knack for building objects of mayhem.

48
00:03:29,010 --> 00:03:32,210
在几年的良好表现后
After a few years, and with some time off for good behavior,

49
00:03:32,610 --> 00:03:36,240
我有机会能继续深造了...
I was given an opportunity to better myself through learning...

50
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:39,640
...通过一个叫学校的奇怪地方
...at a strange place called shool.

51
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:44,410
在那里我再次遇到了大好人先生
It was there that I once again ran into Mr. Goody Two- Shoes.

52
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:48,420
在那里他已经有了他的脑残粉丝团了
He had already amassed a gigantic army of soft- headed groupies.

53
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:56,890
他用美味食物
He bought their affections with showmanship

54
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:59,400
收买友情
and extravagant gifts of deliciousness.

55
00:04:01,870 --> 00:04:06,400
所以我也要做爆米花 然后赢得这群盲目份子的喜爱
So I, too, will make this popp- ed corn and win over those mindless drones.

56
00:04:06,550 --> 00:04:07,940
熄灯
Lights out.

57
00:04:25,730 --> 00:04:28,030
从那时我学到了艰辛的一课:
That's when I learned a very hard lesson:

58
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:30,860
好人总是受到爱戴
Good receives all the praise and adulation,

59
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:33,900
干坏事的就是要去蹲墙角
while evil is sent to quiet- time in the corner.

60
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:38,340
看来我无法合群
So fitting in wasn't really an option.

61
00:04:39,310 --> 00:04:41,780
当他们在学唱儿歌时...
While they were learning the Itsy Bitsy Spider...

62
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:46,950
...我在学习如何将生物脱水然后再按照意愿水化它们
...I learned how to dehydrate animate objects and rehydrate them at will.

63
00:04:48,220 --> 00:04:52,920
有些时候 觉得只有小跟班和我在一起 与全世界为敌
Some days, it felt like it was just me and Minion against the world.

64
00:04:54,390 --> 00:04:56,050
不管我怎么努力
No matter how hard I tried,

65
00:04:56,230 --> 00:04:58,290
我永远都不合群
I was always the odd man out,

66
00:04:58,460 --> 00:05:00,230
是剩下的那个
the last one picked,

67
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,490
永远一团糟 是老鼠屎
the screw- up, the black sheep...

68
00:05:02,740 --> 00:05:04,030
瞄准他! 
Get him!

69
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:05,470
...坏孩子 - 怪胎! 
...the bad boy. - Freak!

70
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:11,570
傻逼! 
Weirdo!

71
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:19,110
这就是我的命运吗? 
Was this my destiny?

72
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:22,010
等等 也许没错
Wait, maybe it was.

73
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:25,990
当坏蛋不就是我最拿手的吗
Being bad is the one thing I'm good at.

74
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:30,260
我恍然大悟 如果我是个坏孩子
Then it hit me: If I was the bad boy,

75
00:05:30,430 --> 00:05:34,420
我就要当最坏的那个
then I was going to be the baddest boy of them all.

76
00:05:36,270 --> 00:05:38,760
我命中注定会成为超级大坏蛋
I was destined to be a super- villain,

77
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:41,570
我们生来就是对手
and we were destined to be rivals.

78
00:05:42,810 --> 00:05:44,670
生死已注定
The die had been cast,

79
00:05:44,810 --> 00:05:49,040
我那不朽史诗般的终身事业就这样开始了
and so began an enduring, epic, lifelong career.

80
00:05:49,210 --> 00:05:51,240
我爱这份工作
And I loved it.

81
00:05:53,220 --> 00:05:55,550
我们的恩怨越来越错综复杂
Our battles quickly got more elaborate.

82
00:05:56,290 --> 00:05:57,720
他赢了几次
He would win some.

83
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:00,360
我也不逊色
I would almost win others.

84
00:06:00,890 --> 00:06:05,830
他的名号是曼城卫士 蛮城的守护者
He took the name Metro Man, defender of Metrocity.

85
00:06:06,130 --> 00:06:09,620
我打算取一个低调点的名字 超级大坏蛋
I decided to pick something a little more humble: Megamind...

86
00:06:10,170 --> 00:06:14,570
不可比拟的英俊的犯罪天才 一切罪恶的主人
...incredibly handsome criminal genius and master of all villainy.

87
00:06:15,170 --> 00:06:21,570
超级大坏蛋

88
00:06:26,090 --> 00:06:28,180
下班了再看 开门
Read on your own time. Open up.

89
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:36,630
- 嘿 - 呸
- Hey! - Boo!

90
00:06:40,630 --> 00:06:41,960
噢 早上好 典狱官
Oh, good morning, Warden.

91
00:06:42,130 --> 00:06:45,070
好消息哦 我改过自新了
Great news: I'm a changed man, and...

92
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:48,970
作为合格的公民 我可以重返社会了
...and I'm ready to re- enter society as a solid citizen.

93
00:06:49,310 --> 00:06:51,540
你是个恶棍 而且永远是个恶棍
You're a villain, and you'll always be a villain.

94
00:06:51,740 --> 00:06:54,370
你根本没有改过 也就别想着离开
You'll never change, and you'll never leave.

95
00:06:54,550 --> 00:06:55,840
你真搞笑
You're fun.

96
00:06:56,020 --> 00:06:57,280
有人给你寄了份礼物
You got a present in the mail.

97
00:06:57,450 --> 00:06:58,810
是狗狗吗
Is it a puppy?

98
00:06:58,980 --> 00:07:04,150
曼城卫士给你的 "希望你珍惜85次无期徒刑的每分每秒"
From Metro Man. "To count every second of your 85 life sentences."

99
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:07,590
真好玩 没想到曼城卫士也会幸灾乐祸
That's funny. Never thought Metro Man was the gloating type.

100
00:07:07,730 --> 00:07:10,460
噢 但他品位的确不错 我帮你保管吧
Oh, but he does have nice taste. I think I'll keep it.

101
00:07:10,630 --> 00:07:12,760
能不能不要拖延我的时间了
Any chance you could give me the time?

102
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:15,870
今天曼城卫士博物馆开放 我不想迟到
I don't want to be late for the opening of the Metro Man Museum.

103
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:19,570
噢 不 看来你要错过了
Oh no. Looks like you're gonna miss it,

104
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:21,640
错过好几千年
by several thousand years.

105
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:24,170
噢 是吗
Oh, am I?

106
00:07:29,380 --> 00:07:32,210
曼城 曼城卫士日快乐
Happy Metro Man Day, Metro City.

107
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:37,250
在这美丽的日子 美丽的城市
It's a beautiful day in beautiful downtown,

108
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:41,520
我们有幸向这个美丽的人致敬 曼城卫士
where we're here to honor a beautiful man, Metro Man.

109
00:07:42,090 --> 00:07:46,260
他的心胸似海洋 但更宽广
His heart is an ocean that's inside a bigger ocean.

110
00:07:46,930 --> 00:07:49,730
这些年 他用他的超视力一直看护着我们
For years he's been watching us with his super- vision,

111
00:07:49,900 --> 00:07:54,430
用他的超能力解救我们 用他那超宽广的爱心照顾我们
saving us with his super- strength and caring for us with his super- heart.

112
00:07:54,810 --> 00:07:57,400
现在我们回报他的时候到了
Now it's our turn to give something back.

113
00:07:57,580 --> 00:07:59,510
这里是洛克斯安 瑞驰
This is Roxanne Ritchi, reporting live

114
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:02,110
在 曼城卫士博物馆落成典礼现场发回的报道
from the dedication of the Metro Man Museum.

115
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,910
喔 好的 刚才他们让你在广播里念的那一段
Wow. OK, the stuff they make you read on- air,

116
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:07,350
真难以置信 都疯狂了
that's un- freaking- believable. It's crazy.

117
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,750
那是我自己写的 哈尔
I wrote that piece myself, Hal.

118
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:11,320
其实我想说的是
What I was trying to say was,

119
00:08:11,490 --> 00:08:14,190
在现代社会里
I can't believe that in our modern society,

120
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:16,850
还能出现艺术的美感真是难得啊
they let, like, actual art get onto the news.

121
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:18,330
补救的不错啊 哈尔
- Nice save, Hal. - What are we...

122
00:08:18,460 --> 00:08:20,590
我们去喝杯咖啡什么的吧
Like, let's just get a coffee or something.

123
00:08:20,770 --> 00:08:23,430
拜托 今天是 曼城卫士节的大日子
Come on, it's time to get in the Metro Man Day spirit.

124
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,000
如果我是曼城卫士的话
Well, if I were Metro Man,

125
00:08:25,140 --> 00:08:27,000
决不会让超级大坏蛋 绑架你那么多次
Megamind wouldn't be kidnapping you all the time.

126
00:08:27,140 --> 00:08:29,510
- 这是最最最重要的事 - 你真贴心 哈尔
- That's the first thing. - That's sweet, Hal.

127
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:32,970
我会像澳洲野犬照顾孩子一样看着你
And I'd be watching you, like a dingo watches a human baby.

128
00:08:33,180 --> 00:08:34,410
好吧 那听起来...
OK, that sounded...

129
00:08:34,580 --> 00:08:36,840
- 好吧 那听起来有点怪 - 是的 确实有一点
- OK, that sounded a little weird. - A little bit. Yeah.

130
00:08:36,980 --> 00:08:39,210
你的鬼脸让我也感到怪怪的
And you're making a weird face, and that's making me feel weird.

131
00:08:39,380 --> 00:08:40,780
重点是 我会看着你就像...
The point is, I would watch you like someone...

132
00:08:42,420 --> 00:08:45,250
不是爱 我们又没恋爱 我不是说我爱你
Not love. We're not in love. I'm not saying I love you.

133
00:08:45,420 --> 00:08:46,650
嘿 不管怎么样 我爱你
Hey, I love you. Whatever.

134
00:08:46,830 --> 00:08:48,760
但是 我又没有说就像我爱着你 我是说...
But I'm not saying like I'm in love with you. I'm saying...

135
00:08:49,530 --> 00:08:51,890
洛克斯安 洛克斯安
Roxanne? Roxaroo?

136
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:06,970
- 什么...什么 - 嘿...
- Whoa... What? - Hey...

137
00:09:07,150 --> 00:09:10,140
好好上班 政府花钱又不是让你游手好闲的
Get back to work. The city doesn't pay you to loaf.

138
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,310
- 不许动! - 同志们 你们要干什么
- Freeze! - Whoa. What are you doing, guys?

139
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:14,280
是我 我是典狱官
It's me! It's the warden.

140
00:09:15,020 --> 00:09:16,450
喂 开门
Hey! Open up!

141
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:26,160
不 你们这些笨蛋 我们被他耍了
No, you fools. He's tricked us.

142
00:09:26,630 --> 00:09:27,760
你说得没错
You were right.

143
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,160
我一直都会是个大坏蛋
I'll always be a villain.

144
00:09:49,290 --> 00:09:51,620
哎呀帅哥 要搭你一程不
Well, hello good- Iooking. Need a lift?

145
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:54,150
当然要啊 你这条聪明绝顶的鱼
Certainly do, you fantastic fish, you.

146
00:09:54,330 --> 00:09:57,820
- 快上车吧 - 我自由了
- Get in the car, you. - I'm free!

147
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,430
是吗
Right?

148
00:09:59,570 --> 00:10:01,560
你送我的手表太赞了 小跟班
Nice work sending me the watch, Minion.

149
00:10:01,730 --> 00:10:04,100
- 那还用说 老板 - 用力打
- You got it, boss. - Punch it!

150
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:07,740
成功 大家一起来举起双手
All right, put your hands in the air.

151
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:16,280
女士们先生们 欢迎曼城卫士
Ladies and gentlemen, your Metro Man!

152
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:19,650
- 你们在等谁 - 曼城卫士! 
- Who's your man? - Metro Man!

153
00:10:20,190 --> 00:10:22,380
是的 曼城! 
Yeah, Metro City!

154
00:10:24,890 --> 00:10:26,650
来吧 举高你们的手
Gimme some. Come on. Give it now.

155
00:10:26,830 --> 00:10:29,690
把手都给我 来吧 很好
Give it to me. Right on. Gimme the good stuff. All right.

156
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,270
嘿 曼城
Hey, Metro City.

157
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:51,670
嘿 嘿
Hey. Hey.

158
00:10:54,020 --> 00:10:56,110
你们都知道 你们都知道 我是很低调的
You know, you know, I just want to bring it down a bit.

159
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:58,380
小伙子们 小点声 谢谢你们 朋友们
Boys, a little lower. Thank you, fellas.

160
00:10:58,560 --> 00:11:00,790
现在来点实际的
Let's get real for a moment.

161
00:11:00,990 --> 00:11:04,220
对的 对的 对的
That's right. That's right. That's right.

162
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:07,920
尽管有了博物馆是非常非常酷的事情
Although getting a whole museum is super- cool, is super- cool,

163
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:11,330
但你们知道我最大荣誉是什么吗
you want to know what the greatest honor you've given me is?

164
00:11:11,470 --> 00:11:14,230
你们真的想知道吗 真的吗
Do you really want to know? Really?

165
00:11:15,570 --> 00:11:16,870
那我来告诉你们
I'll tell you.

166
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:21,450
你们给我的最大荣誉就是...
The greatest honor you've given me is letting me serve you,

167
00:11:21,610 --> 00:11:23,170
...让我为你们服务 帮助曼城的市民
the helpless people of Metro City.

168
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:25,080
每天结束的时候
And at the end of every day,

169
